On Aug 25 2012 at 12:45 PM, we encountered a blue whale cow and calf at 46 55.198 N, W60 04.710 W. Mike James sent pictures to the Mingan Island blue whale research group (Richard Sears, MICS), where they were able to match the cow to the NW Atlantic blue whale catalogue. She is "B373", first sighted in 2001, and then again in 2006 and 2007. Interestingly, her sex was not previously known, but the presence of the calf identifies her as female. The calf was what generated the most excitement, as it is (now) new to science, and is apparently only the 22nd blue whale calf ever sighted for this population in the last 34 years! My pictures of both the cow and calf have apparently been added to the NW Atlantic blue whale catalogue.
